			<ns0:name>dsprin...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101571556652463395731/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">NaCl currently tries to build the gles2 examples and gles2_book examples.  The issue is that the 3D API is changing, and as these examples are updated to track the new API changes, they are not reflected in the NaCl build due to the DEPS structure.  The examples are not part of the Chrome build, nor are they part of any sanctioned Pepper test.

From what I understand, NaCl pulls in a specific revision of Pepper headers from Chromium.  It also pulls in GPU and the GLES2 examples, but using a different revision.  These can get out of sync with each other, resulting in NaCl integration bot failures.

I'm not sure of the best way to fix this.  A couple of suggestions:
1. (Easy, quick): remove the GLES2 demo builds for NaCl.  3D is not supported in M14, and these demos are not built in Chrome.
2. (More difficult): Align the version of the GPU and GLES2 examples with the Pepper header version.

Note: the 3D changes that cause this integration bot breakage are required for M14, according to people on the Pepper team.
